    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-03-17T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-03-17T11:00:00-05:00" n="554"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d554">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51/1546: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Guggenheim</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-03-17T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 17, 1933—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:48 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>19. My telegram No. 18, March 15, 6 p.m. Publicity campaign advocating moratorium
                    on foreign debt payments increasing and appears to have derived encouragement
                    from a rumor given prominence in local press that the President of the United
                    States is favorably disposed thereto.</p>
                <p>Secretary of Finance is quoted as having told newspaper reporters yesterday that
                    although no decision has been taken in the matter the Government is not deaf to
                    the opinions being expressed by the business and industrial elements in the
                    country.</p>
                <p>It may be regarded as significant in this connection that there now appears to be
                    a tightening of opposition in Congress to proposed reduction of next year’s
                    budget to $37,000,000.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Guggenheim</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
